In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims April 15 through April 21, 2018, as National Volunteer Week in the United States. The article highlights the importance of volunteers in strengthening and improving communities. It mentions the various ways volunteers contribute, such as providing services to the elderly, supporting veterans and military families, and helping during natural disasters. The article praises the compassion and dedication of volunteers and encourages all citizens to engage in volunteer service within their communities.